Persian Gulf Stocks: Deyaar Development and Kuwait Finance House

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-08-11T10:25:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/persian-gulf-stocks-deyaar-development-and-kuwait-finance-house.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  rose 0.2
percent at the 2 p.m. close in the emirate, trimming its loss
for the week to 5 percent. Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  slipped
0.5 percent. Saudi Arabia’s market is closed for the weekend.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.        Deyaar Development (DEYAAR)  PJSC rose to the highest in
a week, gaining 4.2 percent to 27.5 fils. The property company
part-owned by Dubai Islamic Bank PJSC returned to profit in the
first half. Net income was 44.4 million dirhams ($12 million)
after a loss of 344 million dirhams a year earlier.        Kuwait Finance House (KFIN)   advanced the most in more
than a week, rising 2.2 percent to 920 fils. The country’s
largest Islamic bank by assets is estimating a gain of $40
million in the fourth-quarter from a stake sale by a unit. The
subsidiary expects to get approval for the sale by the end of
this month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
